		    <title class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">49.109-1</ph> General.</title>
		    <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
			      <p id="d2878e13" class="- topic/p ">When a termination settlement has been negotiated and all required reviews have been obtained, the contractor and the TCO shall execute a settlement agreement on <ph class="- topic/ph ">
					          <xref href="https://www.gsa.gov/forms-library/amendment-solicitationmodification-contract"
                     format="html"
                     scope="external"
                     class="- topic/xref ">Standard Form 30</xref>
				        </ph> (Amendment of Solicitation/Modification of Contract) (see <ph class="- topic/ph ">
					          <xref href="FAR-i1067386.dita#i1067386"
                     base="i1067386"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">49.603</xref>
				        </ph>). The settlement shall cover-</p>
			      <ol id="d2864e28" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d2878e32" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            Any setoffs that the Government has against the contractor that may be applied against the terminated contract and</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d2878e41" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            All settlement proposals of subcontractors, except proposals that are specifically excepted from the agreement and reserved for separate settlement.</p>
				        </li>
			      </ol>
		    </conbody>
